        <p><strong>Notes about transferred credit and compulsary modules</strong></p>
        <p>Where transferred credit is used, less than 240 credits of grades are counted and the thresholds for each degree class are adjusted on a pro rata basis. The tool will attempt to take this into account if you add a module with the amount of transferred credit you have been given and the grade set to 'transferred'. The tool will also allow you to mark a module as 'compulsary' so it will always be counted in the calculation. Note that both cases are notoriously tricky, so always contact the OU to discuss if in any doubt, and never trust the estimates of tools like this alone!</p>


